rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0002
rows.name: This is Brigadier General Jack Vandham,[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0003
rows.name:
Supreme Commander of the Defense Force
of the Colony of New Los Angeles.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0005
rows.name: Where're all these titles coming from?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0006
rows.name: He's trying to lay on some gravitas.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0007
rows.name: He wants to sound like the leader of a huge, organized army.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_SEL0011
rows.name:
Remark that the title is already
starting to grow on you.

rows.label: xs08060100_SEL0021
rows.name:
Joke that the title makes Vandham
sound like an old movie villain.

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0010
rows.name:
"Brigadier General..."
Maybe if he, like, waxed his mustache up a bit?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0011
rows.name:
Heh, well it's just a title. He can call himself
Colonel Square-tache for all I care.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0012
rows.name: If it gets the Ganglion to listen, I'm all for it.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: xs08060100_MSG0013
rows.name:
Great. Now I'll never get
"Colonel Square-tache" out of my head...[ST:wait ]
